line_1: She sits and flow'ry Wreaths she frames;
line_2: Her Conquest ore the Flow'rs proclaims.

line_1: We long for pine apples in frames,
line_2: The sight our foolish heart inflames,

line_1: His oaten reed to rural ditties frames,
line_2: To flocks and rocks, to hills and rills proclaims,
Tricks and pranks and sports and games

line_1: In vain her fondness, the inquiry Frames,
line_2: Guesses in vain, a Thousand things she Names;
And CHURCHILL writes amongst her sov'reign names.

line_1: " But shap'd in twice ten thousand Frames,
Shall every high resolve Devotion frames,
line_2: Be only lifeless sounds and specious names?

line_1: Near to these seats, behold yon slender frames,
line_2: All closely fill'd and mark'd with modern names;
Have they again (as Sacred Song proclaims)
